==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piquant
<hw>Pi"quant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p. pr. of
<ets>piquer</ets> to prick or sting. See <er>Pike</er>.]</ety>
<def>Stimulating to the taste; giving zest; tart; sharp; pungent;
<as>as, a <ex>piquant</ex> anecdote</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧As
<xex>piquant</xex> to the tongue as salt.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Addison.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Piquant</xex> railleries.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Gov. of
Tongue.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piquantly</ent>⟦br⟧
